Description: Excellent condition RG2120x setup with low action and ernie ball 10s. Only one small knick on the bottom of the guitar (see pictures). Very minimal fretware with a TON of life left. The second output jack does not work otherwise everything is in perfect working condition. Comes with tremolo bar and original Ibanez prestige hardshell case. Will only ship within the states. Contact for any information. From the Ibanez WIKI: The RG2120X is an RG series solid body electric guitar model introduced by Ibanez in 2002. It was made in Japan by FujiGen as part of the upscale Prestige line.The RG2120X features a mahogany body bolted to a maple neck with a 24-fret rosewood fingerboard with small offset position markers only at the 12th fret. Components include a pair of humbucking pickups and a double locking tremolo bridge with L.R. Baggs active piezo pickup saddles which offer an acoustic-like tone. Controls consist of a volume, tone and 5-way selector for the magnetic pickups plus a separate volume and 2-band EQ for the piezo along with a 3-way toggle for selecting magnetic pickup only, piezo only or mixed output.For 2003 the Double Lo Pro Edge tremolo was replaced with the new Double Edge Pro and the pickups were changed.
